President Obama met with NATO Secretary General Anders Fogh Rasmussen in the Oval Office to discuss the progress of implementing their shared strategy for Afghanistan and Pakistan. They also discussed goals for the upcoming NATO Summit in Lisbon, including the unveiling of a new NATO Strategic Concept. This concept aims to reinforce the allied commitment to investing in 21st Century capabilities such as missile defense, cyber defense, and civilian-military capabilities. They also discussed the need to reform NATO's structures to make it more agile and efficient in addressing the challenges faced by allied countries today. Additionally, they emphasized NATO's role as the hub of a network of security partnerships that work towards global stability. President Obama expressed his eagerness to continue discussing these issues with Secretary General Rasmussen and other allied and ISAF partner leaders at the November Summit.